  "What corrects myopia (nearsightedness)?": "",
  "A mirror": "",
  "Converging (convex) lens": "",
  "Diverging (concave) lens": "",
  "Myopia (nearsightedness) is corrected with a diverging lens. The diverging lens spreads light before it enters the eye, moving the focal point back onto the retina.": "",
  "What corrects hyperopia (farsightedness)?": "",
  "A pinhole": "",
  "Hyperopia (farsightedness) is corrected with a converging lens that helps the eye focus light from nearby objects onto the retina.": "",
